Then something clicked.

Maybe we make a mistake by asking:

“Where is an idea?”

As though it should have one location.

Where is the water cycle?

It’s nowhere.

And everywhere.

It’s a circulation, not a container.

Maybe some ideas are more like circulations than possessions.

They temporarily condense in books.

Evaporate into conversations.

Freeze into rituals.

Melt into reinterpretations.

Flow into engineering.

Then evaporate again into speculation.

